{
  "texts": [
    "Such open-source initiatives include for instance PsychoPy (Peirce, 2007 (Peirce,, 2008)), Titta (Niehorster, Siu, & Li, 2015), PyGaze (Dalmaijer et al., 2014), OpenSesame (Mathôt et al., 2012), Gaze-Alyze (Berger, Winkels, Lischke, & Höppner, 2012), and GraFIX (Saez de Urabain, Johnson, & Smith, 2015).",
    "Head-restriction by means of e.g., chin-, and forehead rest, is common practice in many types of studies, for instance in reading research.",
    "Why do researchers choose to restrict their participants?",
    "There are many potential reasons: First, some eye trackers require participants to have stabilized heads by design.",
    "For instance, commercial eye trackers like the EyeLink 1000 from SR Research requires head stabilization when used in tower or desktop mode."
  ]
}